Meant to tweet my thoughts about #DoctorStrange after seeing jt last week.
Here’s what thought about the movie and about Marvel
🧵*non-spoiler*
It got me thinking about Marvel and some of the main critiques from its retractors - that all the movies are the same, stylistically, story-wise or both. I would say this is categorically false.
🕸️📸 | Marvel's Spider-Man: Remastered (2020). https://t.co/XuHT9VIVZ1
Before I saw the film, I read a lot of tweets about how this is truly a Sam Raimi film. I was skeptical how much the film would break out of the typical ‘Marvel mold.’

@TigerDroppedOut Its like MCU vs DCEU. One took its time while the other rushed out the door trying to play catch up and burned themselves in the process.

MS trying not to be DCEU

But babyyy let me say I was pleasantly surprised to see that this movie had Sam Raimi’s DNA all up and thru it! He brought all the visual dynamism, kitsch and campy style that he’s known for. It felt like such a stylistic break from Marvel’s other films.

This Dr Strange in particular though felt like a even more radical stylistic shift than anything Marvel has done yet.
I was so taken aback by this visual style in a Marvel movie but in reality it’s exactly what you would expect from the Evil Dead director.

Guardians of the Galaxy would be completely different if not for James Gunn’s particular brand of humor. Same for Taika Waititi’s Thor. Black Panther wouldn’t have been what is was if not for Ryan Coogler. Chloe Zhao’s The Eternals. The Russo brothers etc etc etc

One thing I attribute to Marvel’s success is that they let directors’ visions shine through. It’s still a big media company with a specific brand and that comes with certain boxes that must be checked but the directors of the films still genuinely make them their own.
@RedArcherLive Avengers game moment

The film felt at once very grand while also feeling contained and episodic. Dealt with the vastness of the multiverse while being a relatively capsulated story about a specific incident and specific characters.

Now about the movie specifically (without spoiling).
So fun!! All the hallmarks of a marvel movie but with a horror spin, infused with the kitsch Raimi style. 
It was convoluted at times but never slow or boring. So many great set peices. A few made me exclaim out loud.
